<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="408" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="129.[759,1352,1868,2296]" pageId="129" pageNumber="408">
Subspecies chiapensis considered synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dickey" authorityYear="1928" box="[924,1014,2070,2099]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Peromyscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="129" pageNumber="408" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stirtoni">stirtoni</taxonomicName>
. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="408" type="synonymic_list">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6761204" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6761204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6761204/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="408" startId="129.[760,914,2149,2178]" targetBox="[145,736,1878,2293]" targetPageId="129">
<paragraph blockId="129.[759,1352,1868,2296]" box="[760,1160,2149,2178]" pageId="129" pageNumber="408">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[760,1160,2149,2178]" pageId="129" pageNumber="408">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[759,1352,1868,2296]" box="[761,1330,2184,2217]" pageId="129" pageNumber="408">
<taxonomicName authority="Dickey, 1928" authorityName="Dickey" authorityYear="1928" box="[761,1106,2184,2217]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Rheomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="129" pageNumber="408" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="thomasi" subSpecies="thomasi">R.t.thomasiDickey,1928—EElSalvador.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[759,1352,1868,2296]" lastBlockId="129.[146,1352,2306,3083]" pageId="129" pageNumber="408">
<taxonomicName authority="Dickey, 1928" authorityName="Dickey" authorityYear="1928" box="[761,1093,2224,2257]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Rheomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="129" pageNumber="408" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="thomasi" subSpecies="stirtoni">R. t. stirtoni Dickey, 1928</taxonomicName>
— highlands of SW Mexico, Guatemala, and W El Salvador; it may occur in Honduras.
</paragraph>
</caption>
